  "datePublished": "2026-04-02",
  "description": "Warm-season annual fruiting crop (Physalis philadelphica, 60–75 days to first fruit). Produces small (2–4 cm) berries enclosed in papery calyx husk. Essential characteristic: self-incompatible (requires 2+ plants for cross-pollination). Single isolated plants produce empty husks. Rio Grande Verde (green) and purple cultivars common. Moderate water and fertility. Prolific and disease-resistant relative to tomatoes and peppers. Ideal for salsa verde and fresh salsas.",
